Class:        Aves
Habitat:      Forest
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     5 years
Weight:       0.003 kg
Status:       Varies
Fact:         Only bird that can fly backwards; heart beats 1,260 times per minute

Name:         Blue Whale
Scientific:   Balaenoptera musculus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Ocean
Diet:         Carnivore (krill)
Lifespan:     80 years
Weight:       150000 kg
Status:       Endangered
Fact:         Largest animal ever known; heart is size of a small car

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Monetarism
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Inflation caused primarily by excessive money supply growth
Formula:    MV = PQ
Economist:  Milton Friedman
Example:    Fed raising interest rates to control money supply and inflation

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

